{
  "texts": [
    "We determined the AC-based SET and RESET voltages for achieving the current values as those obtained from the DC I-V measurements (1.5 and 0.1 nA for SET and RESET, respectively).",
    "The mean values of the AC-pulse amplitudes for the SET and RESET operations were 4.3 and -4.9 V, respectively, with an identical standard deviation of 0.1 V. According to Eq. 1, we determined that the coefficient of variations of the operating voltages for SET and RESET were 0.023 and 0.020, respectively (variation, ~2%).",
    "These coefficients reflect the fine distribution characteristics of the operating voltages of our SRM, which is favorable for achieving a high CA operating yield.",
    "Considering advancements in electronic devices, a program latency in the range of hundreds of microseconds is generally deemed significant.",
    "Despite such notable program latency, the read latency of the SRM was measured at below 10 μs, indicating comparatively lower latency 46."
  ]
}